.SH NAME
ifc-to-db-query - Run SQL against an imported DuckDB database


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBifc-to-db query  [sql] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Run a SQL query against an imported DuckDB database and print results.

.PP
Pass the SQL as a positional argument or use --file to read it from a file.
Output defaults to a formatted table; use --output-format to switch to csv,
json, or jsonl for piping into other tools or for agent consumption.

.PP
Use "ifc-to-db schema" to discover available tables and columns.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--file\fP=""
	Read SQL from file instead of positional argument

.PP
\fB--header\fP[=true]
	Include column headers in output

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for query

.PP
\fB--null-value\fP=""
	String to display for NULL values

.PP
\fB--output-format\fP="table"
	Output format: table, csv, json, or jsonl


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--help-json\fP[=false]
	Print help for all commands as machine-readable JSON


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  # Interactive query with table output
  ifc-to-db query model.duckdb "SELECT * FROM properties LIMIT 10"

  # Run SQL from a file, output as CSV
  ifc-to-db query model.duckdb --file query.sql --output-format csv

  # Distinct property sets as JSON lines
  ifc-to-db query model.duckdb "SELECT DISTINCT pset_name FROM properties" --output-format jsonl
.EE


